box2d

Class B2DBone

  • java.lang.Object
    • box2d.B2DBone

  • public class B2DBone
extends java.lang.Object
    A B2DBone connects two B2DJoint instances with a rigid B2DBody. B2DBones have an orientation, therefore a head- and an end-B2DJoint determined by the order during initialisation. This is later necessary when a B2DMuscle has to connect the ends of two B2DBones the right way.

    This class is not involved in the calculations of a World, it is only providing the starting values and properties of a bone.
